item.title: Why did my smoke detector beep twice?
item.description: Answer It‚Äôs time to return to the Midnight Chirps. The majority of smoke detectors are battery-operated or feature a backup battery. When the voltage of these batteries drops below a specific level, the detector notifies us by chirping. A chemical reaction occurs inside the battery, which results in the production of electricity. What does two beeps on a smoke detector signify, just to be clear? Most of the time, when a smoke alarm or carbon monoxide alarm chirps (makes a brief small beep every 2 minutes or so), it indicates that the battery is about to expire.
